        "timestamp": 1682588540
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's true...</p>",
        "id": 353194310,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1682588659
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This construction is very old, it was done by Johannes at the very beginning. I think the honest answer is he was following the book by James rather than Bourbaki. But one can claim this construction is more general because it does not impose completeness and separatedness in one step, and more natural because looking at all Cauchy filters is the most natural thing to do before noticing you don't get a separated result.</p>",
        "id": 353228643,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1682593383
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll answer the other questions later, I'm late for a talk.</p>",
        "id": 353229240,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1682593460
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I see your point, thanks! And will be waiting for your answer when you have time... <span aria-label=\"clock\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f557\" role=\"img\" title=\"clock\">:clock:</span></p>",
        "id": 353236913,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1682594640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"300245\">@Filippo A. E. Nuccio</span>  Sorry I forgot to come back to your question yesterday night. The main answer is you should un-#xy your problem by telling me what you actually want to do. You shouldn't need to think about details of this construction. </p>\n<p>About question 2, the answer is we would get the same map after composition by the projection <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>œÄ</mi><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>X</mi></msub><mo>‚Üí</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>X</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\pi : C_X \\to \\hat X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">œÄ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9468em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9468em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2523em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.1667em;\"><span class=\"mord\">^</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>X</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the space of Cauchy filters on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>. </p>\n<p>About the final question, note your notations are a bit confusing because you use an invisible symbol for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>œÄ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\pi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">œÄ</span></span></span></span>. The answer is still that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y_1 = y_2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> but I don't have a very efficient proof right now, and I suspect we should rather fix your <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XY_problem\">#xy</a> issue than think about an efficient answer.</p>",
        "id": 353728754,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1682671153
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I keep forgetting to say</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Bourbaki uses minimal Cauchy filters (that we call ultrafilters, IIUC)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This isn't correct. There is no Cauchy in the ultrafilter story. The set of ultrafilters on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> depends on no additional structure on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>, no uniform structure, not even a topology. Ultrafilters are generalized singletons in the same way filters are generalized sets.</p>",
        "id": 353729630,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1682671261
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I never think about ultrafilters but I guess this is true. Is it in Mathlib in some form?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">order.filter.ultrafilter</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">open_locale</span> <span class=\"n\">filter</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">instance</span> <span class=\"n\">foo</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nonempty</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ùìü</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ne_bot</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">rwa</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">filter.principal_ne_bot_iff</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚Üê</span> <span class=\"n\">set.nonempty_coe_sort</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">bar</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nonempty</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"bp\">‚Üë</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ultrafilter.of</span> <span class=\"bp\">$</span> <span class=\"bp\">ùìü</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"bp\">ùìü</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚Üî</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚àÉ</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 353767038,
        "sender_full_name": "Oliver Nash",
        "timestamp": 1682675948
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110031\">@Patrick Massot</span> Thanks, it is perhaps true that there is an <code>xy</code>-problem here, but I find the question mathematically interesting <em>per se</em>. At any rate, I will come back and detail you what I am trying to do (Long story short : proving that the Laurent series are isomorphic to the/a completion of rational functions wrt the <code>X</code>-adic topology, I am 85% done but still some bits are left). I really have no time now. Concerning ultrafilters, I meant that \"ultrafilters\" seem to me to correspond to what Bourbaki calls a \"minimal\" filter (this definition has nothing to do with topology or Cauchy neither), no?</p>",
        "id": 353786481,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1682678424
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>They go in opposite directions anyway.</p>",
